column5: Awesome how time flies.You going to have a cell pkg or is there wifi at your camp so I can get hold of you.
At least you have a longer natural beer cooler this season. Don't show Andy and the Professor this picture .you know what they would say ..LOL. PjShorthorn
Truce ? There are no truces in ice outs ..LOL. Everyone be safe out there on opening week. PjShorthorn
Sent you a pm but I hope both

Made a trip to town today and went had look at the dock and ice all gone.Visited a buddy yesterday and he's just south east of Boat island and was also clear there.Looks like a go everywhere if Eagle is open.Within the normal time frame as usuall
Thanks, I'll drive past Eagle May 17. Getting close.
Hate to point out there is ice on the west portions of VBay. Probably will be gone by tomorrow but not an "ice out" in my mind.
From where I was standing there was no ice in sight.SO ice out man.Easily could of put boat in and go fishing
Picture from today around 1 p.m. Could be your eyesight....
I see open water.tough ice fishing out there don't you think.
I'ld like to see you try and fish that shoreline with your boat...

You won't see me fishing there this time of the year.Much better places to fish.Theres lots of open water around.down by panorama drive its pretty much open toward portage bay.we just have different opinions of ice out.i get excited when I see water.
Let's just say you're both right, or else fight it out with boat oars.
